# 🧪 Testing Patterns for Whisky Hikes

## Test Structure Overview

The project follows a comprehensive testing strategy with unit tests, integration tests, and UI tests organized to mirror the main application structure.

## Test Directory Organization

```
test/
├── config/                      # Test configuration and setup
├── data/                        # Data layer tests
│   ├── repositories/            # Repository tests
│   └── services/                # Service tests
├── domain/                      # Domain layer tests
│   └── models/                  # Model tests
├── UI/                          # UI component tests
├── integration/                 # End-to-end tests
├── mocks/                       # Mock objects and test doubles
├── repositories/                # Repository-specific tests
├── services/                    # Service-specific tests
└── run_all_tests.dart          # Main test runner
```

## Test Types and Patterns

### Unit Tests
- **Model Tests**: Test data models, validation, and business logic
- **Service Tests**: Test external service integrations with mocks
- **Repository Tests**: Test data access layer with mocked services
- **Utility Tests**: Test helper functions and utilities

### Integration Tests
- **API Integration**: Test real API endpoints (use test environment)
- **Database Integration**: Test database operations and migrations
- **Payment Flow**: Test complete payment processing workflows
- **Authentication Flow**: Test login/logout and user management

### UI Tests
- **Widget Tests**: Test individual UI components
- **Screen Tests**: Test complete screen functionality
- **Navigation Tests**: Test routing and navigation flows
- **User Interaction Tests**: Test user input and gestures

## Testing Tools and Dependencies

### Core Testing Framework
- **Flutter Test**: Built-in testing framework
- **Mockito**: Mock generation and test doubles
- **Build Runner**: Code generation for mocks

### Test Configuration
- [test_helpers.dart](mdc:test/test_helpers.dart) - Common test utilities
- [test/config/](mdc:test/config/) - Test-specific configuration
- [test/mocks/](mdc:test/mocks/) - Generated mock objects

## Test File Naming Conventions

### Unit Tests
- `*_test.dart` - Standard test files
- `*_simple_test.dart` - Simplified test versions
- `*_mocks.dart` - Generated mock files

### Test Organization
- Test files should mirror the source file structure
- Use descriptive test names that explain the scenario
- Group related tests with `group()` blocks

## Mocking Patterns

### Service Mocks
```dart
// Generate mocks for services
@GenerateMocks([AuthService, PaymentService])
void main() {
  late MockAuthService mockAuthService;
  late MockPaymentService mockPaymentService;
  
  setUp(() {
    mockAuthService = MockAuthService();
    mockPaymentService = MockPaymentService();
  });
}
```

### Repository Mocks
```dart
// Mock repositories for testing business logic
@GenerateMocks([UserRepository, PaymentRepository])
void main() {
  late MockUserRepository mockUserRepository;
  late MockPaymentRepository mockPaymentRepository;
}
```

## Test Data Management

### Sample Data
- Use realistic test data that represents real-world scenarios
- Create test data factories for consistent test setup
- Avoid hardcoded values in tests

### Test Fixtures
- Store test data in dedicated fixture files
- Use JSON fixtures for complex data structures
- Maintain test data separately from test logic

## Test Execution

### Running Tests
```bash
# Run all tests
flutter test

# Run specific test file
flutter test test/UI/auth/login_page_test.dart

# Run tests with coverage
flutter test --coverage

# Run tests in watch mode
flutter test --watch
```

### Test Runner
- [run_all_tests.dart](mdc:test/run_all_tests.dart) - Centralized test execution
- Supports running tests by category or directory
- Provides test summary and reporting

## Test Coverage Goals

### Minimum Coverage Requirements
- **Models**: 100% coverage (business logic)
- **Services**: 90% coverage (external integrations)
- **Repositories**: 95% coverage (data access)
- **UI Components**: 80% coverage (user interactions)
- **Overall Project**: 85% coverage

### Coverage Reporting
- Generate coverage reports with `flutter test --coverage`
- Review uncovered code for critical paths
- Focus on business logic and error handling

## Best Practices

### Test Organization
- Keep tests close to the code they test
- Use descriptive test names that explain the scenario
- Group related tests logically
- Avoid test interdependencies

### Test Data
- Use factories for creating test objects
- Avoid sharing test data between tests
- Clean up test data after each test
- Use realistic but minimal test data

### Assertions
- Test one thing per test method
- Use specific assertions (avoid generic `expect()`)
- Test both positive and negative scenarios
- Verify error conditions and edge cases

### Performance
- Keep tests fast and focused
- Use mocks for external dependencies
- Avoid unnecessary setup and teardown
- Run tests in parallel when possible

## Integration Test Patterns

### Database Tests
- Use test database instances
- Clean up data between tests
- Test database migrations and schema changes
- Verify data integrity constraints

### API Tests
- Mock external services in unit tests
- Use real APIs in integration tests
- Test error handling and retry logic
- Verify API contract compliance

### Payment Flow Tests
- Test complete payment workflows
- Mock Stripe API calls in unit tests
- Test error scenarios and edge cases
- Verify payment state management

## Continuous Integration

### CI/CD Integration
- Run tests on every commit
- Enforce minimum coverage requirements
- Generate and publish coverage reports
- Fail builds on test failures

### Test Environment
- Use separate test databases
- Mock external services in CI
- Ensure test reproducibility
- Clean up test artifacts

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues
- **Mock Generation**: Run `flutter packages pub run build_runner build`
- **Test Dependencies**: Ensure all test dependencies are in `dev_dependencies`
- **Async Tests**: Use proper async/await patterns
- **Test Isolation**: Avoid shared state between tests

### Debug Mode
- Use `flutter test --verbose` for detailed output
- Add debug prints in failing tests
- Use breakpoints in test debugging
- Check test logs for error details
